<promed@promedmail.org>
[Both Bluetongue (BT) and Epizootic hemorrhagic disease (EHD) are
vector-borne viral infections that affect deer and other ruminants in
North America. The viruses are closely related members of the
_Orbivirus_ genus. Of the (at least) 24 serotypes of BT virus (BTV)
and 10 serotypes of EHD virus (EHDV), only 4 BTV and 2 EHD types have
been associated with clinical hemorrhagic diseases in natural or
experimental situations. ProMED would appreciated receiving detailed
information on the reported cases in deer, with special reference to
laboratory confirmation and virus identification.
See moderator's comments in "Epizootic hemorrhagic disease, deer -
USA (VA, OH) 20020914.5310". For further reading - the reader is
referred to Howerth et al,2001, in Infectious diseases of wild
mammals, 3rd edition, Iowa State University Press, Ames, 77 - 97. -
Mod.AS]
